{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "web:first-corinthians.15",
    "translationId": "web",
    "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
    "chapterNumber": 15,
    "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 15",
    "summary": "Source text for 1 Corinthians 15 in World English Bible."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "web:first-corinthians.15.1",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 15:1",
      "text": "Now I declare to you, brothers, the Good News which I preached to you, which also you received, in which you also stand,",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "web:first-corinthians.15.2",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 15:2",
      "text": "by which also you are saved, if you hold firmly the word which I preached to you — unless you believed in vain.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:first-corinthians.15.3",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 15:3",
      "text": "For I delivered to you first of all that which I also received: that Christ died for our sins according to the Scriptures,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:first-corinthians.15.4",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 15:4",
      "text": "that he was buried, that he was raised on the third day according to the Scriptures,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:first-corinthians.15.5",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 15:5",
      "text": "and that he appeared to Cephas, then to the twelve.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:first-corinthians.15.6",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 15:6",
      "text": "Then he appeared to over five hundred brothers at once, most of whom remain until now, but some have also fallen asleep.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:first-corinthians.15.7",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 15:7",
      "text": "Then he appeared to James, then to all the apostles,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:first-corinthians.15.8",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 15:8",
      "text": "and last of all, as to the child born at the wrong time, he appeared to me also.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:first-corinthians.15.9",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 15:9",
      "text": "For I am the least of the apostles, who is not worthy to be called an apostle, because I persecuted the assembly of God.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:first-corinthians.15.10",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 15:10",
      "text": "But by the grace of God I am what I am. His grace which was given to me was not futile, but I worked more than all of them; yet not I, but the grace of God which was with me.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:first-corinthians.15.11",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 15:11",
      "text": "Whether then it is I or they, so we preach, and so you believed.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:first-corinthians.15.12",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 15:12",
      "text": "Now if Christ is preached, that he has been raised from the dead, how do some among you say that there is no resurrection of the dead?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:first-corinthians.15.13",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 15:13",
      "text": "But if there is no resurrection of the dead, neither has Christ been raised.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:first-corinthians.15.14",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 15:14",
      "text": "If Christ has not been raised, then our preaching is in vain and your faith also is in vain.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:first-corinthians.15.15",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 15:15",
      "text": "Yes, we are also found false witnesses of God, because we testified about God that he raised up Christ, whom he didn’ t raise up if it is true that the dead are not raised.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:first-corinthians.15.16",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 15:16",
      "text": "For if the dead aren’t raised, neither has Christ been raised.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:first-corinthians.15.17",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 15:17",
      "text": "If Christ has not been raised, your faith is vain; you are still in your sins.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:first-corinthians.15.18",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 15:18",
      "text": "Then they also who are fallen asleep in Christ have perished.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:first-corinthians.15.19",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 15:19",
      "text": "If we have only hoped in Christ in this life, we are of all men most pitiable.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:first-corinthians.15.20",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 15:20",
      "text": "But now Christ has been raised from the dead. He became the first fruit of those who are asleep.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:first-corinthians.15.21",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 15:21",
      "text": "For since death came by man, the resurrection of the dead also came by man.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:first-corinthians.15.22",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 15:22",
      "text": "For as in Adam all die, so also in Christ all will be made alive.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:first-corinthians.15.23",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 15:23",
      "text": "But each in his own order: Christ the first fruits, then those who are Christ ’s at his coming.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:first-corinthians.15.24",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 15:24",
      "text": "Then the end comes, when he will deliver up the Kingdom to God the Father, when he will have abolished all rule and all authority and power.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:first-corinthians.15.25",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 25,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 15:25",
      "text": "For he must reign until he has put all his enemies under his feet.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:first-corinthians.15.26",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 26,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 15:26",
      "text": "The last enemy that will be abolished is death.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:first-corinthians.15.27",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 27,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 15:27",
      "text": "For, “ He put all things in subjection under his feet.” But when he says, “ All things are put in subjection ”, it is evident that he is excepted who subjected all things to him.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:first-corinthians.15.28",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 28,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 15:28",
      "text": "When all things have been subjected to him, then the Son will also himself be subjected to him who subjected all things to him, that God may be all in all.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:first-corinthians.15.29",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 29,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 15:29",
      "text": "Or else what will they do who are baptized for the dead? If the dead aren’ t raised at all, why then are they baptized for the dead?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:first-corinthians.15.30",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 30,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 15:30",
      "text": "Why do we also stand in jeopardy every hour?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:first-corinthians.15.31",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 31,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 15:31",
      "text": "I affirm, by the boasting in you which I have in Christ Jesus our Lord, I die daily.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:first-corinthians.15.32",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 32,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 15:32",
      "text": "If I fought with animals at Ephesus for human purposes, what does it profit me? If the dead are not raised, then “ let ’s eat and drink, for tomorrow we die.”",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:first-corinthians.15.33",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 33,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 15:33",
      "text": "Don’t be deceived! “ Evil companionships corrupt good morals.”",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:first-corinthians.15.34",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 34,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 15:34",
      "text": "Wake up righteously and don’t sin, for some have no knowledge of God. I say this to your shame.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:first-corinthians.15.35",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 35,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 15:35",
      "text": "But someone will say, “ How are the dead raised?” and, “ With what kind of body do they come?”",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:first-corinthians.15.36",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 36,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 15:36",
      "text": "You foolish one, that which you yourself sow is not made alive unless it dies.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:first-corinthians.15.37",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 37,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 15:37",
      "text": "That which you sow, you don’ t sow the body that will be, but a bare grain, maybe of wheat, or of some other kind.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:first-corinthians.15.38",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 38,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 15:38",
      "text": "But God gives it a body even as it pleased him, and to each seed a body of its own.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:first-corinthians.15.39",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 39,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 15:39",
      "text": "All flesh is not the same flesh, but there is one flesh of men, another flesh of animals, another of fish, and another of birds.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:first-corinthians.15.40",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 40,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 15:40",
      "text": "There are also celestial bodies and terrestrial bodies; but the glory of the celestial differs from that of the terrestrial.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:first-corinthians.15.41",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 41,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 15:41",
      "text": "There is one glory of the sun, another glory of the moon, and another glory of the stars; for one star differs from another star in glory.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:first-corinthians.15.42",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 42,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 15:42",
      "text": "So also is the resurrection of the dead. The body is sown perishable; it is raised imperishable.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:first-corinthians.15.43",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 43,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 15:43",
      "text": "It is sown in dishonor; it is raised in glory. It is sown in weakness; it is raised in power.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:first-corinthians.15.44",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 44,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 15:44",
      "text": "It is sown a natural body; it is raised a spiritual body. There is a natural body and there is also a spiritual body.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:first-corinthians.15.45",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 45,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 15:45",
      "text": "So also it is written, “ The first man Adam became a living soul.” The last Adam became a life-giving spirit.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:first-corinthians.15.46",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 46,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 15:46",
      "text": "However, that which is spiritual isn’ t first, but that which is natural, then that which is spiritual.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:first-corinthians.15.47",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 47,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 15:47",
      "text": "The first man is of the earth, made of dust. The second man is the Lord from heaven.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:first-corinthians.15.48",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 48,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 15:48",
      "text": "As is the one made of dust, such are those who are also made of dust; and as is the heavenly, such are they also that are heavenly.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:first-corinthians.15.49",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 49,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 15:49",
      "text": "As we have borne the image of those made of dust, let ’s also bear the image of the heavenly.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:first-corinthians.15.50",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 50,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 15:50",
      "text": "Now I say this, brothers, that flesh and blood can ’ t inherit God ’s Kingdom; neither does the perishable inherit imperishable.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:first-corinthians.15.51",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 51,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 15:51",
      "text": "Behold, I tell you a mystery. We will not all sleep, but we will all be changed,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:first-corinthians.15.52",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 52,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 15:52",
      "text": "in a moment, in the twinkling of an eye, at the last trumpet. For the trumpet will sound and the dead will be raised incorruptible, and we will be changed.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:first-corinthians.15.53",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 53,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 15:53",
      "text": "For this perishable body must become imperishable, and this mortal must put on immortality.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:first-corinthians.15.54",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 54,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 15:54",
      "text": "But when this perishable body will have become imperishable, and this mortal will have put on immortality, then what is written will happen: “ Death is swallowed up in victory.”",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:first-corinthians.15.55",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 55,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 15:55",
      "text": "“ Death, where is your sting? Hades, where is your victory?”",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:first-corinthians.15.56",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 56,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 15:56",
      "text": "The sting of death is sin, and the power of sin is the law.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:first-corinthians.15.57",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 57,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 15:57",
      "text": "But thanks be to God, who gives us the victory through our Lord Jesus Christ.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:first-corinthians.15.58",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 58,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 15:58",
      "text": "Therefore, my beloved brothers, be steadfast, immovable, always abounding in the Lord ’ s work, because you know that your labor is not in vain in the Lord.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
